  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support cluster response to drought-affected IDPs, through monitoring IDPs inflow and outflow, as well as intention survey, in Herat and Badghis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to critical levels of internal displacement, caused by what is being described as the worst drought in Afghanistan in decades, through this action, IOM&#x2019;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) will continue to implement flow monitoring to identify and register only the newly arriving drought-affected IDP caseload in Herat City, as well as in Qala-e-Naw in Badghis, and share the information with humanitarian partners to facilitate onward registration of newly arriving IDPs into humanitarian assistance programmes and expedite subsequent delivery of assistance. Additionally, DTM will also continue to track the outflow of IDPs returning to their places of origin or into secondary displacement, as well as conduct return intention surveys in locations of displacement to identify the intentions, motivations, needs and concerns of IDPs to enable partners to better integrate the concerns and requirements of potential returnees into return packages and into return strategies in areas of origin to deliver sustainable return solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
